The paper deals with interference alignment in MIMO interfering broadcast channels, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses user selection algorithms, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The use of MIMO technology in the broadcast channel also relates to multimedia systems (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the computational complexity of the algorithms, which is a topic related to computer engineering (cs.CE).
